to the editor it may be novel for the white mountains national forest to play host to wheelchair hikers but wheelchair users desire to use wilderness areas is not rare or new for these trailblazers wheelchairs matter front page aug 17 people with all types of disabilities have been involved in outdoor recreation for at least two decades i have been mobility impaired since birth yet i have made several wilderness trips at the time of my first trip i had never had any experience in outdoor recreation but others were veteran outdoors people both before and after acquiring their disabilities my fellow travelers have included those with many types of physical emotional and medical conditions natural and physical barriers are opportunities for creative improvisation in all instances we follow minimum impact practices to respect the integrity of the environment nina m pan hastings on hudson ny aug 17 2000

